title: EXE code
extract: An EXE file is a type of program that runs in Microsoft Windows. It consists of binary, machine language code that's not designed to be read or written by humans. While it might be possible to edit an EXE file directly in Notepad or another text editor, the process would be tedious and error-prone.Mar 31, 2015
